{"first_name":"Andrew","last_name":"Thomas-Woolf","permalink":"andrew-thomas-woolf","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/andrew-thomas-woolf","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"afekz","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"4Di Capital","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Thu Jun 25 06:27:49 UTC 2009","updated_at":"Wed Oct 13 01:51:37 UTC 2010","overview":"<p>Andrew is an advisor to the <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/financial-organization/4di-capital\" title=\"4Di Capital\">4Di Capital</a> investment team, where he provides support to the investment processes, economic analyses and deal structuring and execution.</p>\n\n<p>Andrew read for a BCom in Information Systems at the <a href=\"http://www.uct.ac.za\" title=\"University of Cape Town\" rel=\"nofollow\">University of Cape Town</a>, is a South African <a href=\"http://www.saica.co.za\" title=\"Chartered Accountant\" rel=\"nofollow\">Chartered Accountant</a>, a <a href=\"http://www.cfainstitute.org/\" title=\"CFA Charterholder\" rel=\"nofollow\">CFA Charterholder</a> and a professional member of the <a href=\"http://www.acm.org\" title=\"Association for Computing Machinery\" rel=\"nofollow\">Association for Computing Machinery</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Andrew has previously worked in middle-market corporate finance and, in a previous life, worked as a software developer, a lecturer and consulted on various information security matters.</p>\n\n<p>He is also a steering committee member of the <a href=\"http://www.siliconcape.com/\" title=\"Silicon Cape initiative\" rel=\"nofollow\">Silicon Cape initiative</a>, a non-profit organisation committed to facilitating and encouraging technology-orientated start-ups in South Africa, where he contributes mainly on regulatory matters affecting these businesses.</p>\n\n<p>He is married to Alicia Thomas-Woolf, has a cat named KittenZ and particularly enjoys piano compositions i